==English==
===Etymology===
First attested in [[w:1822|1822]], from [[Greek]] [[demotikos]] ''common, vulgar'', from [[demos]] ''common people''.

===Adjective===
#Of or for the common people.


===Specialized uses===
# ''demotic greek'': Common or vernacular variety of the modern Greek language
# ''demotic script'': simplified, cursive form of hieroglyphs used 660 BCE until 4th century CE in ancient egypt